    <forecast>
        <area aac="SA_FA001" description="South Australia" type="region">
            <forecast-period start-time-local="2026-06-09T15:55:59+09:30" end-time-local="2026-06-09T15:55:59+09:30" start-time-utc="2026-06-09T06:25:59Z" end-time-utc="2026-06-09T06:25:59Z">
                <text type="warning_summary_footer">For latest warnings go to www.bom.gov.au, subscribe to RSS feeds, call 1300 659 210* or listen for warnings on relevant TV and radio broadcasts.</text>
                <text type="synoptic_situation">A high pressure system over the Tasman Sea is responsible for a ridge hovering over the north of the state. A cold front will slide over the south of SA overnight, while the ridge persists into Thursday. Northerly winds will freshen ahead of a second cold front expected overnight Friday or Saturday morning.</text>
                <text type="product_footer">* Calls to 1300 numbers cost around 27.5c incl. GST, higher from mobiles or public phones.</text>
            </forecast-period>
        </area>
        <area aac="SA_PW014" description="North East Pastoral" type="public-district" parent-aac="SA_FA001">
            <forecast-period index="0" start-time-local="2026-06-09T15:00:00+09:30" end-time-local="2026-06-10T00:00:00+09:30" start-time-utc="2026-06-09T05:30:00Z" end-time-utc="2026-06-09T14:30:00Z">
                <text type="forecast">Clear. Winds northerly 20 to 30 km/h.</text>
            </forecast-period>
            <forecast-period index="1" start-time-local="2026-06-10T00:00:00+09:30" end-time-local="2026-06-11T00:00:00+09:30" start-time-utc="2026-06-09T14:30:00Z" end-time-utc="2026-06-10T14:30:00Z">
                <text type="forecast">Mostly sunny. Slight chance of a shower south of Yunta, most likely in the early morning. Near zero chance of rain elsewhere. Winds northwest to northeasterly 15 to 25 km/h tending northwest to southwesterly 15 to 20 km/h in the early afternoon then becoming light in the late afternoon. Overnight temperatures falling to between 9 and 13 with daytime temperatures reaching 21 to 28.</text>
                <text type="uv_alert">Sun protection 11:00am to 1:20pm, UV Index predicted to reach 3 [Moderate]</text>
            </forecast-period>
            <forecast-period index="2" start-time-local="2026-06-11T00:00:00+09:30" end-time-local="2026-06-12T00:00:00+09:30" start-time-utc="2026-06-10T14:30:00Z" end-time-utc="2026-06-11T14:30:00Z">
                <text type="forecast">Sunny. The chance of morning fog south of Yunta. Light winds becoming east to northeasterly 15 to 25 km/h in the morning. Overnight temperatures falling to between 7 and 12 with daytime temperatures reaching 21 to 29.</text>
            </forecast-period>
            <forecast-period index="3" start-time-local="2026-06-12T00:00:00+09:30" end-time-local="2026-06-13T00:00:00+09:30" start-time-utc="2026-06-11T14:30:00Z" end-time-utc="2026-06-12T14:30:00Z">
                <text type="forecast">Sunny. Winds east to northeasterly 15 to 20 km/h tending north to northeasterly 25 to 35 km/h during the morning then decreasing to 15 to 25 km/h during the afternoon. Overnight temperatures falling to between 9 and 13 with daytime temperatures reaching 23 to 28.</text>
            </forecast-period>
            <forecast-period index="4" start-time-local="2026-06-13T00:00:00+09:30" end-time-local="2026-06-14T00:00:00+09:30" start-time-utc="2026-06-12T14:30:00Z" end-time-utc="2026-06-13T14:30:00Z">
                <text type="forecast">Partly cloudy. Very high chance of showers south of Leigh Creek, slight chance elsewhere. Winds northwest to northeasterly 15 to 25 km/h tending northwest to southwesterly during the day then tending southeast to southwesterly during the afternoon. Overnight temperatures falling to between 12 and 15 with daytime temperatures reaching between 19 and 29.</text>
            </forecast-period>
        </area>
